main event: A radar and visual observation of an unidentified object was reported on 11 Sep 63 in the Pacific.
interesting points: The object was observed for a duration of 8 minutes and 10 seconds., The elevation of the object increased from 40 to 60 degrees during the observation., The object then descended to about 100 feet., The object was moving northeast and displayed variable speed., The object was classified as possibly astronomical or unidentified based on insufficient data.
